cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.IR, cs.LG 

This paper deals with computational methods for identifying borrowed words in social media, which is a task related to natural language processing and computational linguistics. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques and data mining, which are relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed methods in terms of correlation coefficients, which is a statistical measure, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper presents a case study on language identification, which is related to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
